def: Capability of being exhausted.I was seriously tormented by the thought of the exhaustibility ofmusical combinations. J. S. Mill.
The branch of meteorology treating of the automaticregistration of the precipitation of rain, snow, etc.; also, thegraphic presentation of precipitation data.

Of, pertaining to, or derived from, mercury; containingmercury; -- said of those compounds of mercury into which thiselement enters in its lowest proportion. Mercuric chloride, corrosivesublimate. See Corrosive.
One of the speakers in a dialogue. Derham.
The nostril, or one of the nostrils, of whales, porpoises, andallied animals.
Having much intellectual power.-- A`ble-mind"ed*ness, n.
A genus of coleopterous insects, including the glowworms.
A genus of the genus Daphnia.
One of the rudimentary front wings of certain insects(Stylops). They resemble the halteres, or rudimentary hind wings, ofDiptera.
One of a group of lizards having the teeth immovably united tothe top of the alveolar ridge.-- a. Of or pertaining to the acrodonts.
